SMC380H1-F-20225.courseDescription: An opportunity for students to pursue an independent course of study not otherwise available in the Faculty of Arts and Science. Application forms are available from the SMC Principal's Office. Not eligible for CR/NCR option.
SMC380H1-F-20225.prerequisite: Completion of 10.0 credits and written approval of a faculty supervisor and the SMC Principal.

More information can be found here:
https://stmikes.utoronto.ca/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/SMCIndependent_Study_Form_20219.pdf

 

For "E" indicator courses, please contact the SMC Program Administrator, Stephanie Taylor at smc.programs@utoronto.ca (50 St. Joseph Street, Odette Hall, Room 020, St. Michael's College).
SMC380H1-F-20225.deliveryInstructions: Meetings will be determined in consultation with your supervisor.
